al-user`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:3:This directory is the home for the FastAPI application, backend-owned workflow logic, durable\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:12:  - `services/`: backend-owned business logic, including the shared story workflow tool registry\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:18:- `tests/`: backend test suite\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:20:- `Dockerfile`: backend container image\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:48:The settings module merges built-in defaults, `secrets.yaml`, and then `STORYTELLER_*` environment variables. Environment variables win when both sources set the same field. The backend-only Gemini key lives in `secrets.yaml` or the backend process environment and is never sent to the browser.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:57:uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8565\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:68:[`backend/app/db`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/db) and the matching Alembic history\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:69:under [`backend/migrations`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations).\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:74:cd backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:83:cd backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:95:[`backend/tests/integration`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/tests/integration). These\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:102:make backend-integration-test\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:107:`pytest.mark.integration` tests. The default `make backend-test` path keeps skipping these tests so\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:110:Manual invocation from `backend/` is also supported:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:119:Future CI should treat `make backend-integration-test` as the durable-state gate after booting the\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:143:[`backend/app/services/story_tools.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/story_tools.py)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:145:[`backend/app/models/story_tools.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/story_tools.py).\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:152:[`app/data/genre_tone_catalog.yaml`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/data/genre_tone_catalog.yaml)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:156:cd backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:163:cd backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:176:[`backend/app/storage`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/storage). It hides the current\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:182:- `build_object_storage_service(settings)`: build the runtime storage client from backend settings\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:184:- `python -m app.storage.smoke_test`: write and read a sample object through the configured backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:192:make backend-storage-smoke\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:196:shell even when the main Compose backend container uses `http://gcs:4443` internally.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md:202:- `GET /api/hello`: compatibility endpoint kept for the current frontend scaffold\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/scripts/README.md:7:- `bootstrap-dev.sh`: creates `secrets.yaml` if needed, installs repo hooks, prepares `backend/.venv`, and syncs frontend dependencies\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:46:- AI access: Gemini 3.1 family behind backend-owned adapters and services\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:59:- `frontend/` contains a Vite React app served on `http://localhost:8566`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:60:- `backend/` contains a FastAPI app served on `http://localhost:8565`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:74:- creates or refreshes `backend/.venv`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:75:- syncs `frontend/node_modules`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:85:- `frontend` on `http://localhost:8566`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:86:- `backend` on `http://localhost:8565`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:91:`secrets.yaml` is already gitignored and reserved for local-only credentials. `make bootstrap` will create it from `secrets.example.yaml` when needed, but you still need to replace the placeholder Gemini API key before using AI-backed workflows. The repo-managed Git hook blocks accidental commits of `secrets.yaml`, `.env` files, and obvious live key material. The compose file uses development defaults for Postgres and the GCS emulator, while the backend loads secrets from the repo-root `secrets.yaml` at container startup.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:103:- `make bootstrap`: first-run setup for hooks, local Python deps, frontend deps, and a local `secrets.yaml`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:108:- `make format`: apply Prettier to the frontend and Ruff formatting to the backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:110:- `make lint`: run frontend ESLint and backend Ruff lint checks\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:111:- `make test`: run backend pytest and frontend Vitest\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:112:- `make build`: run the frontend production build\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:113:- `make check`: run formatting checks, lint, tests, and the frontend build in one pass\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:114:- `make backend-storage-smoke`: round-trip a sample object through the local storage emulator\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:119:2. make changes in `frontend/` or `backend/`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:126:For frontend-only work, `make frontend-format`, `make frontend-format-check`, `make frontend-lint`, `make frontend-test`, and `make frontend-build` are available as narrower targets. For backend-only work, use `make backend-format`, `make backend-format-check`, `make backend-lint`, `make backend-test`, and `make backend-storage-smoke`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:141:`make reset` removes only those two data volumes so schema or seed-data changes can start from a clean slate without forcing frontend or QA dependency reinstallation. If you intentionally want a full compose wipe, including cached dependency volumes, `./scripts/dev-compose.sh down --volumes` remains available as the deeper reset path.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:143:The backend receives the local infrastructure coordinates through environment variables in Compose:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:153:The backend settings layer merges defaults, `secrets.yaml`, and environment variables in that order. More detail is in [docs/secrets-and-local-config.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md).\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:164:├── backend/\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:179:├── frontend/\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:191:- `frontend/`: browser client and TypeScript UI foundation\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:192:- `backend/`: FastAPI API code, settings, services, tests, worker home, and migration home\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md:207:- the backend and worker own AI access, long-running jobs, and persistent state\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/genre-tone-catalog.md:3:Storyteller's curated genre and tone catalog is backend-owned reference data. The current seed\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/genre-tone-catalog.md:5:[`backend/app/data/genre_tone_catalog.yaml`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/data/genre_tone_catalog.yaml)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/genre-tone-catalog.md:29:- [`prompts/41-tone-selection-api-and-ui.md`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/41-tone-selection-api-and-ui.md): confirms tone choices should be filtered by genre from backend-owned data.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/genre-tone-catalog.md:33:hard-coding new options in the frontend.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/genre-tone-catalog.md:59:make backend-seed-catalog\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/genre-tone-catalog.md:65:cd backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/genre-tone-catalog.md:72:cd backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/genre-tone-catalog.md:84:backend-owned catalog file.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/package.json:2:  \"name\": \"storyteller-frontend\",\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/package.json:7:    \"dev\": \"vite\",\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/package.json:8:    \"build\": \"tsc -b && vite build\",\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/package.json:12:    \"preview\": \"vite preview\",\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/package.json:13:    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/package.json:28:    \"@vitejs/plugin-react\": \"^6.0.1\",\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/package.json:37:    \"vite\": \"^8.0.1\",\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/package.json:38:    \"vitest\": \"^4.1.2\"\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:30:      - -backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:51:  backend:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:53:      context: ../../backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:61:      - ../../backend:/app\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:94:      context: ../../backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:103:      - ../../backend:/app\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:127:  frontend:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:129:      context: ../../frontend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:131:      backend:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:136:      VITE_DEV_PROXY_TARGET: http://backend:8565\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:139:      - ../../frontend:/app\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:140:      - frontend_node_modules:/app/node_modules\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:162:      frontend:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:167:      TARGET_BASE_URL: http://frontend:8566\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:174:  frontend_node_modules:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations/README.md:23:cd backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations/README.md:32:cd backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations/README.md:41:cd backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations/README.md:50:After migrations are applied, seed the backend-owned genre and tone catalog from the application\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations/README.md:54:cd backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/chat-action-echoes.md:39:- The frontend rebuilds transcript echoes from durable history in\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/chat-action-echoes.md:40:  `frontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/frontend-state-architecture.md:3:Prompt 23 introduces a small but explicit split between durable backend data and\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/frontend-state-architecture.md:9:   - `frontend/src/features/session/sessionQueries.ts`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/frontend-state-architecture.md:13:   - `frontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.ts`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/frontend-state-architecture.md:15:     copying the backend snapshot into local state.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/frontend-state-architecture.md:17:   - `frontend/src/features/session/SessionWorkspaceProvider.tsx`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/frontend-state-architecture.md:24:  refresh for backend snapshots.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/README.md:16:- `frontend` on `http://localhost:8566`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/README.md:17:- `backend` on `http://localhost:8565`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/infra/compose/README.md:23:The backend container reads the repo-root `secrets.yaml` through `STORYTELLER_SECRETS_FILE=/workspace/secrets.yaml`, so the local Gemini API key stays server-side even during Compose development.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/README.md:5:The frontend now uses the current Vite React TypeScript baseline as its foundation, then layers in the app shell, route structure, and shared primitives required by the prompt pack.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/README.md:17:- `src/api/`: backend request helpers and service-specific clients\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/README.md:22:- `vite.config.ts`: Vite dev server configuration, including the backend proxy\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/README.md:34:See [docs/frontend-state-architecture.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/frontend-state-architecture.md) for the current split between React Query server state and the workspace-local runtime store.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/README.md:40:- `npm run lint`: lint the frontend source\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/README.md:41:- `npm run test`: run the frontend unit tests\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/README.md:42:- `npm run format`: format the frontend files with Prettier\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:3:Keep changes boring, typed, and easy to review. This repo is split between a React + TypeScript frontend and a FastAPI backend, so use the stack-specific tooling below instead of personal preferences.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:9:- `make lint`: run frontend ESLint and backend Ruff checks\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:10:- `make test`: run backend pytest and frontend Vitest\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:11:- `make check`: run formatting checks, lint, tests, and the frontend production build\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:15:- `make frontend-format`, `make frontend-format-check`, `make frontend-lint`, `make frontend-test`, `make frontend-build`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:16:- `make backend-format`, `make backend-format-check`, `make backend-lint`, `make backend-test`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:17:- `make backend-integration-test` for the real Postgres + fake GCS durability suite\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:28:- Keep FastAPI route handlers thin. Parse input, call a backend-owned service, and return typed response models.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:29:- Put durable workflow logic in backend services or repositories, not in route modules or frontend components.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:31:- Treat the backend as the source of truth for workflow stage, job progress, and AI side effects. The browser reflects state; it does not own it.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:35:- Raise readable, domain-specific backend errors as soon as invalid state is detected; translate them once at the API boundary.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:36:- Return structured error payloads from HTTP endpoints instead of ad hoc strings when the frontend needs to branch on the failure.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:38:- In the frontend, prefer explicit empty, loading, and error states over silent failure.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:42:- Keep hand-written source in `frontend/src/`, `backend/app/`, `backend/tests/`, `docs/`, and `scripts/`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:43:- Treat generated output as disposable. Build artifacts belong in ignored directories such as `frontend/dist/`, coverage caches, or future runtime storage paths under `infra/persistence/`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:45:- Keep AI-produced runtime assets, exported documents, and generated audio in backend-managed storage locations instead of checking them into git.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:49:- Keep fast backend unit coverage under `make backend-test`; do not make that target depend on local infrastructure.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:50:- Put durable-state tests that require Compose-backed Postgres or fake GCS under `backend/tests/integration/` and mark them with `pytest.mark.integration`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md:51:- Reuse `make backend-integration-test` for local validation and future CI jobs so migrations, storage, and queue semantics are exercised the same way everywhere.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/data/background_music/README.md:8:python backend/app/data/background_music/generate_curated_music.py\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:3:This document defines the durable business objects and workflow rules for a single story-creation session. The goal is to give the backend, frontend, migrations, and later AI orchestration code one shared contract for how a session progresses, pauses, rewinds, and resumes.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:8:- Workflow truth lives on the backend, not in browser-only UI state.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:38:`resume_stage` is the key anti-guessing field. The backend computes it from durable stage states so the frontend does not need to infer where to reopen a session by looking at which panels happen to have data.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:83:- `backend/app/models/workflow.py`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:84:- `frontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:86:The backend remains the authority for validating transitions. The frontend should use the same literal IDs for rendering, navigation, and optimistic display only.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:120:- On reopen, the backend should send the earliest stage whose state is not `completed`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:123:This is the behavior implemented by the `resolve_resume_stage` helper in both the backend and frontend contract files.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:156:- If the user decides the plan itself is wrong, they may navigate back to `beats` or `story_setup`, accept changes there, and let the backend mark `composition` and later stages stale.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:176:- Backend authority: `backend/app/models/workflow.py`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:177:- Frontend mirror for rendering and client-side navigation: `frontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/domain-model.md:185:- The backend service layer, not the frontend, decides whether a requested stage transition is valid for the current session snapshot.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:3:This document describes the shared backend registry for story-stage operations that may be called by\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:8:- [`backend/app/models/story_tools.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/story_tools.py)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:9:- [`backend/app/services/story_tools.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/story_tools.py)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:10:- [`backend/app/worker/default_handlers.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/worker/default_handlers.py)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:14:Before prompt 37, the backend had:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:59:Those contracts are exported through [`backend/app/models/__init__.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/__init__.py), so callers do not need to reach into a private module to use them.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:105:[`backend/app/worker/default_handlers.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/worker/default_handlers.py)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:119:the shared tool registry. That gives the LLM-facing layer the same backend vocabulary that workers\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:124:- [`backend/app/ai/intent_parser.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/intent_parser.py)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:125:- [`backend/app/ai/prompts/intent_parser.md`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/prompts/intent_parser.md)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:129:1. Add request and result models in [`backend/app/models/story_tools.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/story_tools.py).\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:130:2. Add a `StoryWorkflowToolDefinition` entry in [`backend/app/services/story_tools.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/story_tools.py).\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/product-brief.md:36:- Sessions are durable backend entities.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/product-brief.md:49:- The model may propose actions, but a deterministic backend policy layer decides whether each action is valid for the session's current stage.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/product-brief.md:74:- AI model family: Gemini 3.1, with backend-owned adapters and centralized model configuration\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/composition-loop-e2e-test.md:3:The backend composition loop now has a focused end-to-end regression test in\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/composition-loop-e2e-test.md:4:`backend/tests/test_story_tools.py`:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/adr/README.md:9:- `0001-core-runtime-architecture.md`: backend-owned AI calls, durable Postgres session state, file-backed GCS assets, websocket live updates, separate workers for long-running jobs, and soft planning constraints\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:8:The backend source of truth lives in `backend/app/models/chat_actions.py`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:9:The mirrored frontend parser and type layer live in\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:10:`frontend/src/features/session/chat/chatToUiActions.ts`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:72:- Auto-apply candidates are still only candidates. The backend policy layer may\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:75:- The frontend mirror rejects payloads that violate the default confirm-first\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:76:  rule so UI suggestions and backend validation start from the same baseline.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:117:The deterministic evaluator now lives in `backend/app/services/action_policy.py`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:118:with typed request and response models in `backend/app/models/action_policy.py`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:120:Two backend entrypoints expose the same engine:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/background-music-mixing.md:9:  `backend/app/data/background_music/`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/background-music-mixing.md:12:- When an audio job starts, the backend resolves those settings into a concrete\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/background-music-mixing.md:18:2. The backend assembles a narration master WAV from the segment assets.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/background-music-mixing.md:19:3. If background music is enabled, the backend writes the narration master to a\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/bedtime-guidelines.md:5:rules and the backend abstractions that carry them into prompts.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/bedtime-guidelines.md:59:The reusable backend source of truth lives in:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/bedtime-guidelines.md:61:- [`backend/app/models/bedtime_guidelines.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/bedtime_guidelines.py)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/bedtime-guidelines.md:62:- [`backend/app/ai/bedtime_guidelines.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/bedtime_guidelines.py)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/bedtime-guidelines.md:66:- `backend/app/models/bedtime_guidelines.py` stores the preset key, active-vs-planned audience\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/bedtime-guidelines.md:68:- `backend/app/ai/bedtime_guidelines.py` renders stage-specific prompt fragments for `pitch`,\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/bedtime-guidelines.md:73:- [`backend/app/ai/pitch_generation.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/pitch_generation.py)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/bedtime-guidelines.md:74:- [`backend/app/ai/character_generation.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/character_generation.py)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/bedtime-guidelines.md:75:- [`backend/app/ai/beat_sheet_generation.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/beat_sheet_generation.py)\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/bedtime-guidelines.md:82:`shared_bedtime_default`, for a broad bedtime read-aloud audience. The backend also stores a plan\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/planning-funnel-e2e-test.md:5:[`backend/tests/test_planning_funnel_e2e.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/tests/test_planning_funnel_e2e.py) drives one session through the planning funnel from genre selection to a saved story setup with a generated chapter outline. The goal is to catch regressions where individually healthy planning endpoints stop composing into one durable user journey.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/planning-funnel-e2e-test.md:26:- It runs in the default backend suite, so the funnel is checked before shipping instead of hiding behind optional integration flags.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/planning-funnel-e2e-test.md:33:- No browser automation is involved; this test covers the backend contract that the workspace UI consumes.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:8:For each segment run, the backend refreshes two context layers:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:22:### 1. AI calls stay on the backend\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:24:All Gemini text, planning, composition, and narration calls belong behind backend-owned adapters and services.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:26:- The browser talks only to backend APIs and websocket streams.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:28:- Model IDs stay centralized in backend settings and adapter code, not in frontend code or route handlers.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:29:- The backend policy layer decides whether a model-suggested action is valid for the current workflow stage before state changes are accepted.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:63:The browser needs live updates during composition and audio generation, and those updates need to remain tied to durable backend state.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:109:- Put websocket endpoints under backend API ownership, not in the frontend dev server.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/system-diagram.md:29:    API -. \"backend-owned model config and policy\" .-> Gemini\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/event-taxonomy.md:18:  - `service`: synchronous backend orchestration that is not best described as user or worker.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/event-taxonomy.md:22:The backend centralizes these names in `backend/app/models/events.py` as `SessionEventType`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/event-taxonomy.md:39:Known event types use typed Pydantic payload models in `backend/app/models/events.py`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/event-taxonomy.md:85:The primary append/read surface is `backend/app/services/event_log.py`.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/event-taxonomy.md:102:`backend/app/repositories/events.py`. It is responsible for per-session sequencing and\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md:3:Storyteller loads backend configuration from two sources:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md:32:The backend looks for `secrets.yaml` in this order:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md:36:3. `backend/`\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md:41:The Docker Compose backend service mounts the repository at `/workspace` and sets:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md:57:Then replace `gemini.api_key` with a real local key before starting the backend.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md:69:`secrets.yaml` uses the same nested structure as the backend settings object:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md:147:Startup fails fast when required values are missing or malformed. The backend reports a short error list instead of a long Python traceback when launched with:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md:153:The frontend never receives the Gemini API key. The browser only talks to the FastAPI backend, and all Gemini access stays in backend-owned services and adapters.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md:11:Storyteller is a full-stack application with a browser client, a backend-owned workflow engine, durable relational state, durable object storage, and resumable background jobs.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md:38:4. Provider flexibility: keeping Gemini behind backend adapters lets the app keep a stable internal interface while model IDs, structured output tactics, or narration providers evolve.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md:40:The frontend should only call the backend's API and subscribe to backend-owned progress events.\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md:55:The target backend should separate concerns explicitly:\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md:91:- `frontend/`: Vite React TypeScript app\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md:92:- `backend/`: FastAPI app with an app factory, versioned routers, settings loader, workflow models,\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md:94:- `backend/migrations/`: Alembic home for database schema history\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md:95:- `backend/app/worker/`: reserved home for background job runners\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md:96:- `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`: local frontend, backend, PostgreSQL, file-backed GCS emulator, and browser QA services\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
